    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out per the MRL 2 requirements matrix. Validation results demonstrate RH prediction accuracy within acceptance criteria across all five operating points. The UQ campaign (128-run Latin hypercube sampling and parametric rotational-speed sweeps) confirmed robustness of hemolysis predictions to input variability; findings are summarised in validation result narratives VR-01 and VR-02. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory decision that the CFD model identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. Decision: Accepted.",
